All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
App
The App class serves as the main entry point for the Hotel Manager application.
CheckinCommand
The CheckinCommand class implements the Command interface and handles the check-in process for a hotel room.
CheckoutCommand
The CheckoutCommand class implements the Command interface and handles the checkout process for a hotel room.
Command
Represents a command that can be executed.
CommandFactory
Factory class responsible for creating Command objects based on user input.
ExitCommand
The ExitCommand class implements the Command interface and provides functionality for exiting the application.
Guest
Represents a guest with personal details including PESEL, name, and surname.
Hotel
Represents a hotel with a specified name, number of floors, and number of rooms per floor.
ListCommand
The ListCommand class implements the Command interface and provides functionality for listing all rooms and their availability.
Map<K,V>
The Map interface represents a mapping of keys to values.
MyMap<K,V>
The MyMap class provides a simple implementation of the Map interface using two ArrayLists to store keys and their corresponding values.
PricesCommand
The PricesCommand class represents a command that displays the prices of all rooms in a hotel.
Room
Represents a hotel room with attributes such as room number, price per night, maximum guest capacity, and registered guests.
SaveCommand
The SaveCommand class implements the Command interface and is responsible for saving the current state of the hotel's guests into an Excel file.
UnknownCommand
The UnknownCommand class implements the Command interface and handles cases where an unrecognized command is entered.
ViewCommand
The ViewCommand class implements the Command interface and allows the user to view detailed information about a specific hotel room.
